        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 12:55PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 1255 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Edgewood, or 10 miles northeast of Wills Point, moving
northeast at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Emory and Lake Fork Reservoir around 100 PM CDT.
Sulphur Springs around 115 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Martin Springs,
Weaver, Tira, New Birthright, Flora, Flats, Nelta, Hermits Cove, and
Dike.

This includes Interstate 30 between mile markers 117 and 138.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
